    <body>
        <title>Adding a new documentation set</title>
        <understanding>
            <p>A documentation set (<xml-element-name>doc-set</xml-element-name>) groups one or more related topic sets into a complete document. For example, a website could be a single doc-set composed of topic sets to group related web pages.</p>
       </understanding>
       <planning>
           <planning-question>
                <planning-question-title>Do I need a doc-set?</planning-question-title>
                <planning-question-body>
                    <p>You need a doc-set to group related topic-sets into a single document.</p>
                </planning-question-body>
                <how-to-answer-body>
                    <p>While you can put all your topics into a single <feature>topic set</feature>, if you use a doc-set with muli\tiple topic-sets, you can present your topic-sets in a specific order in the document output.</p>
                </how-to-answer-body>
            </planning-question>
       </planning>
        <doing>        
            <p>A doc-set is specified in the <feature>SPFE configuration file</feature> used to build the documents. You cannot define a doc-set in a separate file and use an include element to incorporate it. A doc-set must have at least one topic-set.You need the following mandatory elements:
            </p>
            <ul>
                <li>
                    <p><xml-element-name>id</xml-element-name></p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><xml-element-name>title</xml-element-name>: The title of the doc-set to display </p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><xml-element-name>topic-set-type-order</xml-element-name>: The order in which the topic-sets are shown in the document output.</p>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <p><xml-element-name>topic-sets</xml-element-name>: The list of topic-sets to include in the doc-set</p>
                </li>    
            </ul>
        </doing>
